8. How is True Solid State LiDAR different from traditional LiDAR technology?
True Solid State LiDAR uses solid-state components, such as semiconductor lasers, to emit and receive laser Git Hubs, whereas traditional LiDAR uses mechanical spinning parts to achieve the same functionality.

